<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-69-0293 </DOCNO><TEXT>At Thailand's Mae Moh generating station, Unit 8, the first of four 300-MWsteam generators, will become operational in 1989. The new unit is aforced-circulation, radiant-reheat, balanced-draft design with a single-celltower furnace. Design specifications are based on experience gained fromearlier units fueled by lignite. The Mae Moh generators will be the firststeam generators in the Far East to be equipped with an advanced ashmonitoring system. 1 fig.</TEXT></DOC>